			<div class="content" id="post-content-4862627">
									

<p>Hello! This is my first attempt to get reviewed on anything so forgive me if it's not quite the correct format!</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content"><img src="http://news.blrstage.com/app/uploads/sites/3/2017/06/Paperwork.jpg" alt="Paperwork.jpg" class="image" /></div>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Seeking Greenlights:</strong> Yes</p>
<p><strong>Page Type:</strong> SCP Article</p>
<p><strong>Genre (Optional):</strong> Other (paradoxical)</p>
<p><strong>Elevator Pitch:</strong> So it is thought to be a telepathic entity as the &quot;voice&quot; is never recorded, though it is &quot;heard&quot;. Sometimes it is &quot;seen&quot; however, witness accounts differ so much it is not clear whether there are multiple entities, it changes appearance, or the witnesses are subject to a form of hysteria &quot;if you stare into a dark room ling enough, you will eventually see something&quot;</p>
<p>My thought is that the entity gets some form of nourishment by it's host acting counter to their normal behavior and it is even more valuable if the host doesn't acknowledge the entity's existance at all. Denial of its existance is good, but not as good as complete ignorance.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Central Narrative:</strong> It needs to be visited each day and the subject must remain with the entity long enough to confirm that it is in fact still contained. There is a real danger of the entity escaping sue to its nature of wanting to be forgotten, and it may have been once or twice and had it's containment treated as an &quot;empty&quot; chamber, allowing it to escape.</p>
<p>To contain, the entity will be visited by a subject each day.<br />
The subject will be given a myriad of monotonous tasks to be completed with a large amount of inocuous restrictions placed on them. The reasoning is to give the entity a large amount of non-dangerous things to tempt the subject with and avoid another D-508905 incident.</p>
<p><strong>Hook/Attention-Grabber:</strong> &quot;could be responsible for some of the most brutal dictators and serial killers who claim to be hearing voices or enacting god's will&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;something that thrives by convincing it's host that it does not exist.&quot;</p>
<p><strong>Additional Notes:</strong> I figure that it will operate within the confines of suggestions available. Starting off small, but desiring a much larger payoff when available. Biding it's time while it &quot;grooms&quot; it's host into more severe self-contradictions.</p>
<p>I imagine Euclid for it's classification.</p>
<p>Please tell me what you think :) i hope i can start being a real contributer soon! ^^</p>
</div>
