					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/quadraginta" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6391595); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6391595&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610216302" alt="Quadraginta" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6391595)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/quadraginta" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6391595); return false;" >Quadraginta</a></span> <span class="odate time_1610212435 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">09 Jan 2021 17:13</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4866119">
									

<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Placeholder</span></p>
<p>Heyo, I'm here. Let's take a look, shall we?</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+Let's&nbsp;do&nbsp;it!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-Let's&nbsp;do&nbsp;it!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><span style="font-size:1.3em;"><strong>The Elevator Pitch</strong></span></p>
<p>I find the Elevator Pitch to be too bland and not fleshed out enough. You're playing with the fears of something lurking in the dark—which is a primal human fear that we've felt since it's literally necessary for our survival—as well as added anomalous voices coming from the dark, which may or may not be telepathic.</p>
<p>Essentially, your anomaly boils down to, 'a mysterious hunter in the dark that works best when either ignored or never noticed.'</p>
<p>The 'never noticed' bit kinda falls flat when it starts&#8230;trying to talk to people.</p>
<p><span style="font-size:1.3em;"><strong>The Central Narrative</strong></span></p>
<blockquote>
<p>It needs to be visited each day and the subject must remain with the entity long enough to confirm that it is in fact still contained.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Some very Series 1-esque 'obey it and bow down to its whim or suffer' vibes here.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The reasoning is to give the entity a large amount of non-dangerous things to tempt the subject with and avoid another D-508905 incident.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>First, tell us what the D-508905 incident is, if it's even relevant.</p>
<p>Second, so, it doesn't even care if the people do dangerous things, or if they just feel creeped out?</p>
<p>That's not very threatening.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;could be responsible for some of the most brutal dictators and serial killers who claim to be hearing voices or enacting god's will&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;something that thrives by convincing it's host that it does not exist.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I could see this going places, but the overall concept at the moment falls much too flat at what it's trying to achieve.</p>
<p>It's a creepy thing in the dark that goes bump in the night. What is it? Creepy. What does it do? Makes you act out of character. Too underdeveloped.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My thought is that the entity gets some form of nourishment by it's host acting counter to their normal behavior</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Well, expand on that.</p>
<p>Apologies if this was harsh, but so far, this feels like an underdeveloped creepypasta that was developed during some 'shower thoughts' in the afternoon.</p>
<p>Every bit of it needs expansion. The only bit I really, really liked was this:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>if you stare into a dark room long enough, you will eventually see something</p>
</blockquote>
<p>^^<br />
Try to capture that feeling of creepiness and fear we all instinctively know and work it into an SCP.</p>
<p>Remember, all SCPs nowadays need a story of some kind.</p>
<p>Considering you thought about this in the first place, I'm going to assume you had some weird, freaky experience in the dark? I know I did. I'm sure we all did.</p>
<p>Draw some inspiration from that. Think of some people that this anomaly tormented and write a story around that.</p>
<p>Simply sticking something in a cell and giving us basic D-Class containment logs and attempts doesn't really work anymore.</p>
<p>Anywho, I hope I helped and I bid you a lovely day o7</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

